            <thetext>Just experienced the following problem: Due to an application bug, qooxdoo threw an exception saying &quot;[Class] has no themeable property &#39;icon&#39;&quot;.

The consequence was that the entire dialog that the application tried to open was rendered invisible, i. e. the DIVs were present and receiving f. i. mouse clicks, but they were transparent.

qooxdoo UI rendering ought to be error-tolerant enough to recover after an exception, so that the application can limp on instead of totally falling apart.

-&gt; Fabian, as discussed.</thetext>
